description:
During World War II, The Archon was a Nazi sympathizer who ruled the small country of Lutzany. He conducted experiments on humans seeking to create an army of supermen. In the process, he created The Mark, a superhuman nearly as powerful as he. The Mark and The Archon battled. Thinking he had won, The Mark traveled the world to crush acts of genocide wherever he found them.

However, The Archon survived and, with Captain Midnight jettisoned into the future, was able to gain control over the two largest weapons manufacturers in the world: Sharkbyte and Albright Industries, Captain Midnight's tech company. Helping him along the way were Chuck Ramsey, and the villains Fury Shark, Phang, and Tempus.

deck: Having recurring dreams he can't explain, Corbin must now face the biggest drug case of his law enforcement career. Although things don't go according to plan, Corbin discovers what it means to become "Awakened".
description:
Origin

Corbin was born October 2, 1996, not much is known about Corbin’s parents. Corbin’s mother was found lying next to him on the door steps of an Orphanage in Irvine, CA. Corbin’s mother had been stabbed and died before help could arrive. When Corbin was found, a note reading: “His name is Corbin, please watch over him; please keep him safe...” When Corbin would ask about his parents, the orphanage staff would tell Corbin his mother died saving his life. At age 7 Corbin, along with several other children, was experimented on with Human performance enhancers. After the children were released, at age 8, Corbin was adopted to a middle aged married couple by the name of Mr. Charles Reed, and Tasha Reed. It seemed Corbin had finally found loving parents, and took the last name of his new family. At the age of 18, Corbin graduated from High School with honors, and pursued a career in law enforcement. At the age of 21 Corbin graduates from the Police Academy, and becomes a police officer for the city of Faulkom. Shortly after, Corbin’s father passes away from cancer. Now alone, Corbin’s mother needs constant attention due to her old age, and is placed in an assisted living community. In the year 2019 at the age of 23 Corbin is promoted to Corporal and transferred to the Narcotics unit. Corbin has repressed memories of the experiments that were done to him and sometimes has flashes and reoccurring dreams during the day of the events, although he can’t remember what the experiments or dreams are from, they still haunt him. Now at the age of 24 Corbin still works in the Narcotics unit. The flashes and/or dreams are becoming more frequent and are starting to effect his profession. Corbin is beginning to mature into the last remaining “Awakened” and the story begins.

Creation

Corbin Reed was created in 2007, when Joshua Skidmore, was driving to work. Josh had been working on basis of Corbin's character for over 4 years before deciding to proceed with Corbin as he is now. Corbin's creation stemmed from parts of Josh's personal life. before venturing into the comic book profession, Josh spent some time in law enforcement, where a lot of character aspects derive from. Corbin was thought to be a lawful good type character struggling to find himself, although Corbin was an orphan, the events of his past make him who he is as an adult. Corbin's background was then expanded when co-creators Stacie Renee' and Brett Keith joined Josh and began development of "The Awakened" series giving Corbin a more human feel rather than superhero. Corbin is in a sense the comic book version of Josh. Model/Actor Wade Baker plays the role of Corbin perfectly.

Personality

Corbin is easy going and gets the job done. He takes pride in what he does and has a sense of humor yet feels responsible when things go wrong. Has a pretty long fuse but when he is done that’s when you see the temper. He will take most anything but he wears his heart on his sleeve. He is an open book to those that know him. Being adopted he feels that he always has to one up the abilities he has on the force to make them proud and that his parents will never stop loving him. He has a fear of intimacy due to his childhood and his profession as a cop. He has repressed memories which cause him to bottle up his emotions.

Character Profile

Real Name: Corbin Matthew Reed

Occupation: Corporal with the Faulkom City Police Department Narcotics Division

Height: 5'11"

Weight: 165 lbs

Hair: Brown

Eyes: Hazel

Base: Faulkom City, CA

Partnerships: Ashlyn Beringer, Darren Wink.

Foes: Lee Stevens, Teslacorp.

First Appearance: The Awakened # 1 (August 2014)

Created by: Joshua Skidmore, Stacie Renee' and Brett Keith

Powers and Abilities

Corbin didn't have any special super human abilities, until he awakened and gained several powers from the "human Performance Enhancers" tested on him as a child.

Fire Control

Upon awakening, Corbin now can generate fire at will from his body, being able to generate fire has its benefits, such as, Corbin is now immune to fire effects such as heat as well as flames themselves. Corbin's body absorbs it now. While concentrating Corbin's clothes as well as anything he is in contact with can sustain the same fire resistance and consistency as his body. People, Corbin comes into contact with may also share in his fire generating ability if he so chooses to concentrate on that person. Corbin also has the ability to generate balls of fire as well as explosions, creating fire weapons he can throw and/or shoot.

Healing Factor

Now that Corbin is awakened he has a healing factor that has a mind of its own. Corbin's body and mind can heal themselves without Corbin being aware or conscious. Other awakened hybrids may hurt Corbin but the only way to truly kill an "Awakened" is by cutting off their head, due to fast regeneration.

Agility/Strength

Corbin's agility is now off the chart, from running faster than a standard human to jumping higher, even Corbin's strength and endurance is far superior to that of an average human. when it comes to lifting weight, Corbin can now as an awakened lift approximately 730 kg (1609 lb), which is the equivalent to the average 21st century Smart Car.

Awakening

During a house raid, Corbin and his team are ambushed and killed, leaving Corbin as the sole survivor. While dealing with the deaths of his entire team and abandonment of his right hand man, Taylor, Corbin begins to smolder and glow. Unaware of his physical changes, Corbin is confronted by the shooter. Upon speaking to the unidentified person Corbin awakens for the first time and bursts into flames, then passes out, causing the house he had been in to explode and catch fire.

Dreams

Corbin continues to have very lucid dreams which always end the same. The dreams become more and more frequent as Corbin matures more and more into becoming "Awakened". Later, Corbin learns that these "dreams" are really repressed memories from when he was being experimented on at the orphanage as a child.
name: Corbin Reed

deck: Ashlyn isn't your typical female comic charater, Ashlyn can hold her own in a fight and is very independent.  Since losing her parents and becoming "Awakened" Ashlyn is a force not to be messed with.
description:
Origin

Ashlyn was born April 16, 1998, in the State of Colorado, to a Mr. John Beringer (only child), and Ms. Kate Beringer (only child). Ashlyn was the child of a single father; her mother had died giving birth to her. Ashlyn’s father was enlisted in the United States Army, and had completed 2 tours in Iraq during Operation Iraqi Freedom in which started March 20, 2003. As a child Ashlyn’s father used to teach her survival training, military tactics, and combat. Shortly after starting his second tour in early 2004, Ashlyn’s father and his unit were killed in action by an I.E.D. (Improvised Explosive Device). Ashlyn was now 6 years old. With Ashlyn’s father now dead, Ashlyn was placed into an orphanage. At the orphanage, Ashlyn, along with several other children were experimented on with Human performance enhancers (See "The Awakened" story-line for further). After the children were released, Ashlyn disappeared staying off the grid, alone, until she matured and became an Awakened at the age of 20. Ashlyn honed her new skills and used it to her advantage (steal, con, etc.) to survive in the city. When Teslacorp took over the old orphanage property (See Teslacorp. Story-line), their agents began tracking down the potential “Awakened”. Ashlyn was eventually captured and tortured. Ashlyn had escaped and was recaptured several times throughout the years. At the age of 21, Ashlyn escapes from Teslacorp. for a final time after hearing their plans to track down the remaining “Awakened” and harvest their power. After a year of searching Ashlyn now 22 years of age, tracks down the last remaining potential “Awakened” Corbin, and the story begins.

Creation

When creating Ashlyn, Creator Joshua Skidmore wanted a more plausible 21st century woman, one who could hold her own in a superhero world and not constantly scream for help like so many female love interests in the comic world. Ashlyn was created for that purpose, she is the love interest of the main character Corbin Reed, but also someone who doesn't really need saving, she is seen as an equal when it comes to fighting. Ashlyn was also decided to have the "Awakened" ability of water, making her adaptive to situations as well as beautiful but deadly water like qualities. When co-creators Stacie Renee' and Brett Keith went over the character, she was much further developed as far as personality and attitude. Model/Actress Deidre Rozay plays the role of Ashlyn perfectly

Personality

Ashlyn plays tough. She takes pride in what she does and has a sense of humor yet has no patients and expects things to be done in a fast manner. She has a soft side which she rarely shows but is easily seen by Corbin. Bottles everything inside and pretends everything is always okay. Ashlyn is constantly looking for an escape route and objects to use as weapons. Very military oriented. Thinks the world is out to get her. Ashlyn is a bit of a perfectionist and conspiracy theorist.

Character Profile

Eyes: Blue

Upon awakening, Ashlyn now can generate water at will from her body, being able to generate water has its benefits, such as, Ashlyn is now immune to water effects such as drowning as well as water it'self. Ashlyn's body absorbs it now. While concentrating Ashlyn's clothes as well as anything she is in contact with can sustain the same water resistance and consistency as her body. People, Ashlyn comes into contact with may also share in her water generating ability if she so chooses to concentrate on that person. Ashlyn also has the ability to generate balls of water as well as water currents, creating water weapons she can throw and/or shoot.

Ashlyn has a healing factor that has a mind of its own. Ashlyn's body and mind can heal themselves without her being aware or conscious. Other awakened hybrids may hurt Ashlyn but the only way to truly kill an "Awakened" is by cutting off their head, due to fast regeneration.

Ashlyn's agility is now off the chart, from running faster than a standard human to jumping higher, even Ashlyn's strength and endurance is far superior to that of an average human. when it comes to lifting weight, Ashlyn can now lift approximately 730 kg (1609 lb), which is the equivalent to the average 21st century Smart Car.

deck: Now an "Awakened" Darren is the oldest of 12 individuals experimented on with military grade human performance enhancers.   There are a total of 6 males and 6 females.  Over time Darren has lost his path and fallen into darkness.
description:
Origin

Darren was born August 28, 1993, in the State of Washington, to a Mr. Doug Wink, and Ms. Joann Wink. Darren’s mother worked as a Paramedic. Darren’s father was a Computer Software Engineer. As a child Darren used to get picked on due to his scrawny appearance. Darren would usually get into fights at school on a weekly basis and have to take a different route home from school everyday just to avoid trouble. At night Darren would fall asleep to the sound of his parents fighting and arguing, about money and spending time with the family. One particular night when Darren was 8 years old he could hear his parents fighting as usual, when all of a sudden he heard a loud bang. When Darren crept down the stairs to see where the noise had come from, he saw his father lying on the floor in a pool of blood; Darren’s father had been shot to death, and as Darren called out to his father from the top of the stairs he saw his mother put a gun to her head and pull the trigger. Darren had just witnessed his mother kill his father, then commit suicide. Now all alone, Darren was placed into an Orphanage. At the orphanage, Darren, along with several other children were experimented on with Human performance enhancers (See "The Awakened" story-line for further). After the children were released, Darren was eventually adopted at the age of 12 by an elderly couple, but Darren kept to himself. At age 15, Darren began lifting weights and learning self defense, eventually becoming a hit man for various clients at the age of 24. At the age of 25 Darren became an Awakened. When Teslacorp. took over the old orphanage property (See Orphanage history), their agents began tracking down the potential “Awakened”. And Darren was eventually found and hired by Teslacorp. as the ultimate security, and also to monitor him for harvesting at a later time. One year later Darren is 27 years old, the oldest of the “Awakened” and the story begins.

Creation

When Creator Joshua Skidmore was in the process of creating Darren, thoughts of having a mentally scared person came to mind. Creating a character who was flawed more than others and had painful memories of the trauma he had suffered as a child, seemed more "human" and allowed the reader to relate more too. Co-creators Stacie Renee' and Brett Keith also had a hand in Darren's creation, making his personality and demeanor more aggressive than the other characters. Darren also draws from his childhood relationships with Corbin Reed and Ashlyn Beringer, making him a force to be taken seriously. Model/Actor Curtis J. Moore plays the role of Darren perfectly.

Personality

Darren is angry at the world. He takes his job and believed “purpose” very seriously. Feels alone, and responsible for not being able to stop or save his parents. He has a hard time trusting people, and because of that he keeps to himself. Believes the human race are a kind of “disease”, and has no problem exterminating them if need be. He goes where the money is. He has a softer side but it is buried deep within, and it is dormant. As a child Darren was the protector of the children when he was at the orphanage, and feels partially responsible for the experiments due to not being able to stop them and protect the children. He still has the feeling of responsibility towards protecting the defenseless, but it has been buried beneath all rage, hate and abuse.

Character Profile

Darren can generate Earth/Rock at will from his body, being able to generate Earth/Rock has its benefits, such as, Darren is now immune to Earth/Rock effects such as stone-like surfaces as well as Rock or Earth themselves. Darren's body absorbs it now. While concentrating Darren's clothes as well as anything he is in contact with can sustain the same Earth/Rock resistance and consistency as his body. People, Darren comes into contact with may also share in his Earth/Rock generating ability if he so chooses to concentrate on that person. Darren also has the ability to merge with stone-like objects and use them as weapons or as projectiles, Darren can even go as far as changing the size and shape of his limbs.

Healing Factor

Darren has a healing factor that has a mind of its own. Darren's body and mind can heal themselves without Darren being aware or conscious. Other awakened hybrids may hurt Darren but the only way to truly kill an "Awakened" is by cutting off their head, due to fast regeneration.

Agility/Strength

Darren's agility is now off the chart, from running faster than a standard human to jumping higher, even Darren's strength and endurance is far superior to that of an average human. when it comes to lifting weight, Darren can lift approximately 11793.4 kg (13 tons), which is the equivalent to the average 21st century School Bus, making Darren the strongest of "The Awakened".

Awakening

deck: In a time when the world is seeking an alternative power source, Lee starts a corporation that will test enhanced humans referred to as "Awakened". Lee, being the C.E.O. begins to grow an obsession with these individuals.
description:
Origin

Lee was born June 22, 1975, in the State of Alabama, to a Mr. Bill Stevens, and Ms. Martha Stevens. Lee’s Father was an Oil Tycoon, who retired at the age of 50. Lee’s mother wasn’t really a mother at all, always gone spending the family fortune on frivolous objects. As a child, Lee would often imitate his father, dreaming of one day becoming just like him. However Lee’s father would often be caught up in his own hobbies and interests that Lee would often have a babysitter or live in Nanny. At age 14 Lee Graduated High School, and at age 25 Graduated from Auburn University at the top of his class with a PHD in Biochemistry. In order to make his parents pay attention to him and “love him” Lee felt he needed to impress them with money, or knowledge. In 2016 at the age of 41 Lee becomes CEO of Teslacorp., who is the current leader in alternative energy, and decides to move the corporation to California for better recourses. Several months later Teslacorp. buys and old abandoned Orphanage as the new site for their corporate headquarters. While restoring the orphanage Agents of Teslacorp. come across confidential documents, explaining several secret experiments including the experiments conducted on the orphans before being shut down by the government. Seeing these documents Lee now is convinced the “Awakened” can provide the ultimate unlimited energy source and seeks the test subjects out, and spends the next several years searching. The year is now 2020.

Creation

Creators Joshua Skidmore, Stacie Renee' and Brett Keith, wanted to create a character that could be seen as dealing with the current global situations like "alternative power sources" it gives the reader a sense of connection and sympathy for the "villain" of the story. Most people in today's society would say Lee was doing humanity a service, "For the greater good." This allows Lee to be ruthless and unforgiving and still draw the attention of the reader, almost like an internal battle, the reader,not knowing if they should take the hero or the villain's side. Lee's past also plays a big role in his creation, as the creators did with character Darren Wink, they wanted more humanity in the character, making them more flawed like everyday people. Model/Actor Stephen T. McGovern plays this role perfectly.

Character Profile

Real Name: Lee Stevens

Occupation: C.E.O. of Teslacorp.

Height: 6'0"

Weight: 170 lbs

Hair: Black

Eyes: Hazel

Base: Irvine, CA

Partnerships: N/A

Foes: Corbin Reed, Ashlyn Beringer

First Appearance: The Awakened # 1 (August 2014)

Created by: Joshua Skidmore, Stacie Renee' and Brett Keith

Personality

Lee is extremely smart, he is a perfectionist and believes everyone is beneath him. He has no remorse for people, no sense of charity. He is egotistical, and self idolizing. He believes money, makes the man. Doesn't believe in friendship and thinks everyone just wants to use him for money and political power. Lee tries to prove his worth by being the best at everything he does. He’s obsessive over projects such as the search for the “Awakened”. He believes if he fails his father would reject him.

Powers and Abilities

Intellect

Although Lee doesn't have abilities, his intelligence alone could be considered one. Lee's I.Q. is far off the charters, Graduating earlier than most individuals, Lee was able to create his own empire at a young age and far surpass his generation. Lee's intelligence is unmatched even when compared to his father.

Combat/Swordsmanship

As a child Lee was forced to take several skill building classes such as fencing and a style of Ninjutsu known as Michinoku Ryu. As he grew up Lee decided to stick with these courses and is now considered a master in both swordplay and Ninjutsu. Due to Lee's expert knowledge in these fields, he is extremely lethal and unforgiving in combat.
name: Lee Stevens

deck: As a seasoned Officer, Taylor creates a name for himself, but takes a turn down a possible dark path due to personal issues
description:
Origin

Taylor was born January 23, 1997, to a Mr. Bruce Graham, and Mrs. Karen Graham, and little brother to Garrett Graham by 10 years. Taylor’s Parents were the ideal Mother and Father figure, always spending family time with the kids and taking them on family outings. When Taylor was a child his older brother began to travel down a dark road towards crime. At first just stealing candy, but that quickly escalated to grand theft and drugs as well as getting mixed up with the wrong crowd. Seeing his brother act this way bothered Taylor to the point that he and Garrett hated each other. At the age of 16 Taylor decided to dedicate his life to law enforcement and prevent others from traveling the road his brother had taken. At the age of 20 Taylor graduates from the Faulkom City Police Academy and shortly after turns 21. Corbin Reed and Taylor quickly become friends and as Corbin promotes to Corporal, Taylor becomes Corbin’s right hand man. The year is now 2020, at the age of 23, Taylor found himself starting to travel down a path similar to his brothers. Unknown even to Corbin, Taylor makes some unwise decisions which end up costing him severely.
name: Taylor Graham
